consume

public OUTCOME_TYPE consume(Instance<OUTCOME_TYPE> instance)
                     throws CleartkException
Description copied from interface: InstanceConsumer
Consume the instance and return the outcome (classification) assigned to the instance. If the consumer does not assign outcomes to instances (e.g. a training data consumer), this method should return null.

Parameters:
instance - The instance (features and label) to be consumed.
Returns:
The assigned outcome (classification), or null if an outcome was not assigned.
Throws:
CleartkException

expectsOutcomes

public boolean expectsOutcomes()
Description copied from interface: InstanceConsumer
This method provides an annotation handler (or anything else using an InstanceConsumer) a way to determine whether or not the instance consumer expects the Instances it consumes to have outcomes. For example, if your instance consumer corresponds to a training data writer, then it will expect outcomes. However, if your instance consumer is ClassifierAnnotator, then it will not expect outcomes and therefore your annotation handler should not bother worrying about whether the instances is passes to the consume method have outcomes or not. This method says nothing about whether values are returned from consume.

Returns:
true if the consumer expects the classification Instances to have outcomes, and false otherwise.
